###########################################################

# Arguments [defaults] -> Can be abbreviated to shortest unambiguous prefixes

# For details on arguments and the output generated, please use the help option (-h, --help) with the script:
  % python3 script.py -h

###########################################################

# Accessing and Processing UniProt data files

1] Grab the latest UniProt data with:
  % wget https://ftp.uniprot.org/pub/databases/uniprot/current_release/knowledgebase/complete/uniprot_sprot.dat.gz

2] Uncompress with:
  % gzip -d uniprot_sprot.dat.gz

3] Parse UniProt data to produce output files with:
  % python3 Uniprot_parser.py --inUniprot uniprot_sprot.dat --outPrimAC uniprot_main.tsv --outSecAC uniprot_secondary.tsv ---outGeneID geneID.tsv


###########################################################

# Accessing Protein-Protein Interaction Data

1] Grab the Protein-Protein Interaction Data in miTAB format (2.5 or 2.7)

    - Get BioGRID data (Release Version: 4.4.206) with:
      % wget https://downloads.thebiogrid.org/Download/BioGRID/Release-Archive/BIOGRID-4.4.206/BIOGRID-ORGANISM-4.4.206.mitab.zip

    - Unzip with:
      % unzip BIOGRID-ORGANISM-4.4.206.mitab.zip

    - This will produce one miTAB file per Organism (Use BIOGRID-ORGANISM-Homo_sapiens-4.4.206.mitab.txt for human data)

    - If you want to grab the latest BioGRID data, visit (https://downloads.thebiogrid.org/BioGRID) and navigate to Current-Release


    - Get IntAct data (Latest version) with:
      % wget ftp://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/intact/current/psimitab/intact.zip

    - Once downloaded, unzip with:
      % unzip intact.zip

    - This will produce 2 files (intact.txt & intact_negative.txt). Use intact.txt for further steps


2.1] Parse BioGRID data with:
    % python3 Interaction_parser.py --inInteraction BIOGRID-ORGANISM-Homo_sapiens-4.4.206.mitab.txt --inPrimAC uniprot_main.tsv --inSecAC uniprot_secondary.tsv --inGeneID geneID.tsv > curated_Biogrid.tsv

2.2] Then, parse Intact data with:
    % python3 Interaction_parser.py --inInteraction intact.txt --inPrimAC uniprot_main.tsv --inSecAC uniprot_secondary.tsv --inGeneID geneID.tsv > curated_Intact.tsv


###########################################################

# Building a High-Quality Human Interactome with:
  % python3 Interactome.py --inCuratedFile curated_Biogrid.tsv curated_Intact.tsv --inPrimAC uniprot_main.tsv --inCanonicalFile canonicalTranscripts_*.tsv > Interactome_human.tsv

###########################################################

